msgid "Galactic NH (nhtot)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../usage/nhtot.rst:7
msgid ""
"This page is a work in progress.  See :func:`jinwu.core.utils.nhtot` for "
"the complete API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../usage/nhtot.rst:10
msgid ""
"The ``nhtot`` function queries the Swift UKSSDC nhtot web service to "
"obtain the **total** Galactic hydrogen column density using the method of"
" Willingale et al. (2013, MNRAS, 431, 394)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../usage/nhtot.rst:14
msgid ""
"This includes: - **NHI** — atomic hydrogen (from 21-cm surveys) - **NH₂**"
" — molecular hydrogen (estimated from dust reddening E(B-V)) - **NH,tot**"
" = NHI + 2×NH₂"
msgstr ""

#: ../../usage/nhtot.rst:20
msgid "Why nhtot?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../usage/nhtot.rst:22
msgid ""
"HEASoft's ``nh`` tool returns NHI **only** (from the HI4PI map). At low "
"Galactic latitudes (|b| < 20°), molecular hydrogen contributes "
"significantly, and using NHI-only values in ``tbabs`` (which assumes 20% "
"molecular fraction) systematically underestimates Galactic absorption."
msgstr ""

#: ../../usage/nhtot.rst:27
msgid ""
"The Swift community (including Valan et al. 2023) uses ``nhtot`` for the "
"Galactic component of X-ray spectral fitting."
msgstr ""

